Then I'd actually have to make
it through your writing. Clark.

161
00:14:16.815 --> 00:14:18.942
Knowledge is worth many sacrifices.

162
00:14:19.026 --> 00:14:19.818
That isn't one of them.

163
00:14:19.902 --> 00:14:21.737
Ha. ha. ha. Very funny. Lois.

164
00:14:21.820 --> 00:14:23.697
- Oh. my God.
- He's so fine.

165
00:14:23.780 --> 00:14:26.742
Twenty-two people in the hospital.
over 20 million in property damage.

166
00:14:26.825 --> 00:14:28.744
- It does make you wonder.
- Wonder what?

167
00:14:28.827 --> 00:14:31.872
As great as he is. maybe Superman
didn't completely think through

168
00:14:31.955 --> 00:14:33.498
the ramifications of the Boravia thing.

169
00:14:33.582 --> 00:14:35.751
If this guy is even from Boravia.

170
00:14:35.834 --> 00:14:37.961
What do you mean?
His name is "the Hammer of Boravia."

171
00:14:38.045 --> 00:14:40.380
Yeah. I doubt his parents named him that. Jimmy.

172
00:14:40.464 --> 00:14:42.549
We have no clue what his actual goal was here.

173
00:14:42.633 --> 00:14:45.010
I think it's pretty obvious the
goal was kicking Superman's ass.

174
00:14:45.093 --> 00:14:47.054
Uh. he did... He didn't
completely kick Superman's ass.

175
00:14:47.137 --> 00:14:48.096
Pretty thoroughly. Clark.

176
00:14:48.180 --> 00:14:51.975
<i>Show me! You show me
what ties there are</i>

177
00:14:52.059 --> 00:14:55.062
<i>between Boravia and this "Hammer!"</i>

178
00:14:55.145 --> 00:14:57.397
Yeah. see. Superman did say
he thought the. uh. Hammer

179
00:14:57.481 --> 00:14:58.982
might be faking a Boravian accent.

180
00:14:59.441 --> 00:15:00.442
Superman said that?

181
00:15:00.525 --> 00:15:02.569
Yeah. I interviewed him
right afterwards. Great guy.

182
00:15:03.070 --> 00:15:06.740
You know. it's funny that you keep getting
all these interviews with Superman. Clark.

183
00:15:06.823 --> 00:15:09.534
I don't think there's anything funny
about good journalism. Lois.

184
00:15:09.910 --> 00:15:10.953
Uh-huh.

185
00:15:11.036 --> 00:15:16.083
<i>The relationship
between Boravia and United States</i>

186
00:15:16.166 --> 00:15:20.087
<i>has been like iron for 30 years.</i>

187
00:15:20.420 --> 00:15:23.590
<i>until Superman came along.</i>

188
00:15:26.051 --> 00:15:27.678
<i>What you're looking at. my friends.</i>

189
00:15:27.761 --> 00:15:31.431
<i>is the most powerful being on Planet Earth:</i>

190
00:15:32.307 --> 00:15:33.809
Ultraman.

191
00:15:34.434 --> 00:15:35.811
You created this man?

192
00:15:35.894 --> 00:15:38.981
Ooh. Check this out. The Engineer.

193
00:15:39.064 --> 00:15:41.608
A former special operative. whose blood I infused

194
00:15:41.692 --> 00:15:44.111
with microscopic machines called "nanites."

195
00:15:44.444 --> 00:15:47.906
which she can form into anything she can imagine.

196
00:15:48.365 --> 00:15:52.703
And. of course. you're familiar with
my flying armored forces. the Raptors.

197
00:15:52.786 --> 00:15:57.666
All together. they're an unstoppable force
we call PlanetWatch.

198
00:15:59.084 --> 00:16:02.504
More than capable of containing
any otherworldly threat.

199
00:16:04.881 --> 00:16:07.092
So you want the Defense Department

200
00:16:07.175 --> 00:16:10.679
to hire your metahumans
to take down the Kryptonian?

201
00:16:10.762 --> 00:16:14.349
After Superman acted with violence
against our Boravian allies.

202
00:16:14.433 --> 00:16:15.475
I think it'd be worth considering.

203
00:16:15.559 --> 00:16:17.436
Big Blue stopped a war.

204
00:16:17.519 --> 00:16:19.229
Naive. maybe. but well-intentioned.

205
00:16:19.313 --> 00:16:23.734
Well. I don't know the intentions
of an unattended firehose. General Flag.

206
00:16:23.817 --> 00:16:26.153
I just do what I can not to be splashed.

207
00:16:26.236 --> 00:16:29.156
- Mr. Luthor...
- The disarming Director Crawley.

208
00:16:29.239 --> 00:16:31.241
The country of Boravia has purchased

209
00:16:31.325 --> 00:16:33.493
over 80 billion dollars' worth of arms

210
00:16:33.577 --> 00:16:35.662
from LuthorCorp in the past two years.

211
00:16:35.954 --> 00:16:37.456
- And?
- And no one would profit more

212
00:16:37.539 --> 00:16:40.250
from a war with Boravia and Jarhanpur than you.

213
00:16:40.334 --> 00:16:42.627
A cynic might say that having
Superman out of the way

214
00:16:42.711 --> 00:16:43.962
might not be bad for business.

215
00:16:44.046 --> 00:16:46.923
Well. what's particularly
bad for business is dying.

216
00:16:47.257 --> 00:16:50.093
And I have a distinct feeling
that's where we're all headed

217
00:16:50.177 --> 00:16:51.636
with the Kryptonian running wild.

218
00:16:51.720 --> 00:16:53.972
So we're gonna lock up all metahumans now?

219
00:16:54.056 --> 00:16:56.433
Look. other metahumans
aren't going off half-cocked.

220
00:16:56.516 --> 00:16:58.226
