Courts decided those rights don't apply

762
00:50:37.202 --> 00:50:38.912
to extraterrestrial organisms.

763
00:50:38.995 --> 00:50:40.330
Therefore. at this point. Superman.

764
00:50:40.413 --> 00:50:42.040
you don't have any rights to read.

765
00:50:42.457 --> 00:50:43.625
The government is very well aware

766
00:50:43.708 --> 00:50:45.585
of the potential limitations detaining you.

767
00:50:45.668 --> 00:50:47.212
so we've outsourced your confinement

768
00:50:47.295 --> 00:50:49.547
and your interrogation to PlanetWatch.

769
00:50:49.631 --> 00:50:50.715
PlanetWatch?

770
00:50:51.716 --> 00:50:53.259
I'm sorry about this.

771
00:51:34.384 --> 00:51:35.260
Hey!

772
00:52:01.453 --> 00:52:03.538
Twice in two days.
What a pleasure.

773
00:52:04.247 --> 00:52:05.248
Luthor.

774
00:52:06.332 --> 00:52:08.501
Your obsession with me
is getting a little creepy.

775
00:52:08.585 --> 00:52:11.463
Don't worry. Tall. dark.
and Martian isn't my type.

776
00:52:11.546 --> 00:52:13.548
- Kryptonian.
- Eh. same diff.

777
00:52:22.599 --> 00:52:23.766
where are we?

778
00:52:23.850 --> 00:52:25.351
A pocket universe.

779
00:52:25.435 --> 00:52:28.146
I replicated the Big Bang
with a LuthorCorp mega-collider.

780
00:52:28.229 --> 00:52:31.107
tearing a tiny hole between
the two universal fabrics.

781
00:52:32.066 --> 00:52:35.028
I'm able to access it from
multiple dimensional portals

782
00:52:35.111 --> 00:52:36.321
I've set up around the globe.

783
00:52:37.322 --> 00:52:40.909
Rex. the metahuman known as the Element Man.

784
00:52:40.992 --> 00:52:43.703
has been called into service
for a specific purpose.

785
00:52:43.786 --> 00:52:46.539
He can metamorphose into any known substance.

786
00:52:46.623 --> 00:52:51.503
Even substances foreign to this planet. like...

787
00:52:58.676 --> 00:53:00.470
Kryptonite.

788
00:53:03.598 --> 00:53:05.934
<i>Once again. Vasil Ghurkos is sending troops</i>

789
00:53:06.017 --> 00:53:07.810
<i>to the Jarhanpurian border.</i>

790
00:53:07.894 --> 00:53:08.895
Superman's been out of commission

791
00:53:08.978 --> 00:53:11.481
less than a day. and already
Boravia's pulling this crap?

792
00:53:12.482 --> 00:53:13.816
- Right?
- What?

793
00:53:13.900 --> 00:53:15.276
Sorry. I'm trying to figure out

794
00:53:15.360 --> 00:53:17.612
how Lex Luthor's connected to all this.

795
00:53:17.695 --> 00:53:18.613
How's that a mystery?

796
00:53:18.696 --> 00:53:21.407
LuthorCorp sells arms
to Boravia. Boravia goes to war.

797
00:53:21.491 --> 00:53:24.118
Luthor sells more arms and gets richer than ever.

798
00:53:24.202 --> 00:53:25.870
- Nope.
- No?

799
00:53:25.954 --> 00:53:27.080
Uh-uh.

800
00:53:27.580 --> 00:53:29.249
I have a connection at BodaBank.

801
00:53:29.332 --> 00:53:32.544
Boda handles the transactions
between LuthorCorp and Boravia.

802
00:53:32.627 --> 00:53:33.962
Yes. LuthorCorp sold them

803
00:53:34.045 --> 00:53:35.922
approximately 80 billion dollars' worth of arms.

804
00:53:36.005 --> 00:53:37.048
but for those arms.

805
00:53:37.131 --> 00:53:40.426
Boravia paid only
1.625 billion dollars.

806
00:53:40.510 --> 00:53:42.804
So Luthor gave them arms
for free? For what?

807
00:53:42.887 --> 00:53:47.517
That's the 78 billion.
375-million-dollar question.

808
00:53:47.600 --> 00:53:48.977
Have you found out
where they're holding Superman?

809
00:53:49.060 --> 00:53:50.853
No one in the government'll say.

810
00:53:50.937 --> 00:53:53.314
Luthor seems to be working to disable Superman

811
00:53:53.398 --> 00:53:56.276
just so he can't stop the invasion of Jarhanpur.

812
00:53:56.359 --> 00:53:57.068
Why?

813
00:53:57.610 --> 00:53:59.279
That's way too much sugar. Lois.

814
00:53:59.362 --> 00:54:01.948
I party like a rock star. choir boy.

815
00:54:02.031 --> 00:54:03.950
Still can't hide the taste of petroleum.

816
00:54:04.367 --> 00:54:05.326
God!

817
00:54:22.427 --> 00:54:24.220
Lex is holding Superman in a pocket universe.

818
00:54:24.304 --> 00:54:25.346
A what?

819
00:54:25.430 --> 00:54:26.639
I don't know what a pocket universe is.

820
00:54:26.723 --> 00:54:27.849
Neither does my source.

821
00:54:27.932 --> 00:54:30.101
They don't know anything about anything. really.

822
00:54:30.184 --> 00:54:32.270
But for sure he's in a pocket universe.

823
00:54:32.353 --> 00:54:33.438
Who's your source?

824
00:54:33.521 --> 00:54:35.773
I can't say. but you owe me.

825
00:54:36.274 --> 00:54:37.191
Big time.

826
00:54:37.900 --> 00:54:38.860
Like...

827
00:54:40.486 --> 00:54:42.739
I can't even tell you how big.

828
00:54:45.617 --> 00:54:47.660
I love you. Jimmy Olsen.

829
00:54:47.744 --> 00:54:49.203
- I love you.
- Love you.

830
00:55:03.384 --> 00:55:06.387
Just my Monkey-Bots here. farming outrage 24/7.

831
00:55:06.471 --> 00:55:08.014
Trashing you online.

832
00:55:08.473 --> 00:55:10.099
Hashtag Supershit.

833
00:55:20.777 --> 00:55:22.153
Krypto.

834
00:55:24.864 --> 00:55:26.866
How do you contain a super dog?

835
00:55:28.201 --> 00:55:30.286
You beam super squirrels into its brain.

836
00:55:32.163 --> 00:55:33.998
We'll learn what we can.

837
00:55:34.916 --> 00:55:38.252
Then we'll put the varmint down.

838
00:55:39.128 --> 00:55:40.880
It will undoubtedly be painful.

839
00:55:41.881 --> 00:55:44.092
Mr. Luthor. please!
I swear...

840
00:55:44.175 --> 00:55:46.928
This is our private correctional institution.

841
00:55:47.345 --> 00:55:49.555
Yeah. most cells are rented out to governments

842
00:55:49.639 --> 00:55:51.808
who want to keep their incarcerations

843
00:55:51.891 --> 00:55:54.519
of political agitators private.

844
00:55:54.602 --> 00:55:57.188
Others are for more personal transgressions.

845
00:55:57.522 --> 00:55:59.148
Fleurette wrote a blog about me.

846
00:55:59.232 --> 00:56:00.650
There are few things I hate

847
00:56:00.733 --> 00:56:03.277
more than petty ex-girlfriends.

848
00:56:04.153 --> 00:56:05.530
You wouldn't be telling me any of this if you...

849
00:56:05.613 --> 00:56:08.032
If we ever planned
on letting you out? No.

850
00:56:09.617 --> 00:56:11.828
You'd be terminated already if it was up to me.

851
00:56:12.245 --> 00:56:13.871
First. the government has some
questions they want answered.

852
00:56:17.542 --> 00:56:20.461
Rex. Look who it is.

853
00:56:29.303 --> 00:56:31.264
You be sure to keep our guest in check.

854
00:56:31.347 --> 00:56:33.766
Little Joseph certainly
wouldn't want it any other way.

855
00:56:35.017 --> 00:56:37.228
I'll be back tomorrow to get the answers we need.

856
00:56:41.649 --> 00:56:44.152
Hey. handsome.

857
00:56:48.030 --> 00:56:49.407
Come on over.

858
00:57:01.711 --> 00:57:03.588
- Hi!
- Hey. Eve.

859
00:57:03.671 --> 00:57:04.922
Oh. sorry we had to meet here.

860
00:57:05.006 --> 00:57:07.133
but Lex is always accessing traffic cameras.

861
00:57:07.216 --> 00:57:08.009
so he knows where I am.

862
00:57:08.092 --> 00:57:10.178
I really don't understand why
you stay in that relationship.

863
00:57:10.261 --> 00:57:12.346
'Cause he made a point to tell
me about all his ex-girlfriends

864
00:57:12.430 --> 00:57:14.307
he had imprisoned in his pocket universe.

865
00:57:14.390 --> 00:57:15.892
- What?
- Right?

866
00:57:15.975 --> 00:57:17.894
- How's your mom?
- My mom?

867
00:57:17.977 --> 00:57:19.020
Oh. I love her so much.

868
00:57:19.103 --> 00:57:21.689
I think of her as my mom.
even more than my own mother.

869
00:57:21.773 --> 00:57:23.274
Oh. she feels the same way.

870
00:57:23.357 --> 00:57:25.443
from the-the one time that you guys met.

871
00:57:25.526 --> 00:57:26.944
- Yeah?
- So. hey. Okay.

872
00:57:27.028 --> 00:57:28.738
- Yes. Yes.
- Eve?

873
00:57:28.821 --> 00:57:30.198
There seems to be some sort of connection

874
00:57:30.281 --> 00:57:32.450
between Boravia and your boyfriend.

875
00:57:32.533 --> 00:57:33.659
- I'm not clear on what...
- Oh.

876
00:57:33.993 --> 00:57:34.786
What's wrong?

877
00:57:35.328 --> 00:57:36.496
What's "oh"?

878
00:57:36.829 --> 00:57:39.081
I thought you wanted to see me. Jimmy.

879
00:57:39.165 --> 00:57:40.166
I do but. Eve.

880
00:57:40.249 --> 00:57:43.211
how could I even really see you
with Lex still in the picture?

881
00:57:43.294 --> 00:57:45.046
You're just trying to get information out of me.

882
00:57:45.129 --> 00:57:46.255
I swear to God. that's not it.

883
00:57:46.339 --> 00:57:48.466
I-I just know that if I could
get some real dirt on him.

884
00:57:48.549 --> 00:57:50.092
then maybe the two of us could...

885
00:57:50.176 --> 00:57:51.636
Could be together again?

886
00:57:57.475 --> 00:57:58.476
Yeah.

887
00:58:00.186 --> 00:58:01.395
But you said my toes look like

888
00:58:01.479 --> 00:58:03.064
someone spilled shrimp cocktail on the floor.

889
00:58:03.147 --> 00:58:05.274
You have unconventional toes.
Who cares?

890
00:58:05.358 --> 00:58:06.484
There's other parts of you that people would

891
00:58:06.567 --> 00:58:08.319
find very attractive.

892
00:58:08.402 --> 00:58:10.154
Lex tortured a dog the other day.

893
00:58:10.822 --> 00:58:12.865
- Jesus Christ!
- I know.

894
00:58:12.949 --> 00:58:14.617
- I have to go.
- Eve.

895
00:58:15.535 --> 00:58:17.036
Please see what you can find out.

896
00:58:18.120 --> 00:58:20.456
- Okay.
- Yes! Yes!

897
00:58:21.791 --> 00:58:22.875
Okay.

898
00:58:25.503 --> 00:58:26.838
I'm-I'm putting 'em in my pocket.

899
00:58:26.921 --> 00:58:28.589
Okay.

900
00:58:38.599 --> 00:58:40.893
Joseph. He's your son?

901
00:58:40.977 --> 00:58:41.978
Don't talk to me.

902
00:58:42.645 --> 00:58:43.437
Please.

903
00:58:45.690 --> 00:58:48.901
I could fly over and get him if you just...

904
00:58:48.985 --> 00:58:49.986
if you'd stop with the Kryptonite.

905
00:58:50.069 --> 00:58:52.280
There's no way out of here.
okay? So. just...

906
00:58:52.363 --> 00:58:54.282
- There's always a way.
- I said don't talk to me!

907
00:58:55.741 --> 00:58:56.492
I told you.

908
00:58:58.703 --> 00:59:00.162
Don't talk to me!

909
00:59:10.256 --> 00:59:11.507
Yeah. so what do you want me to do?

910
00:59:11.591 --> 00:59:12.592
Where's the creamer?

911
00:59:12.675 --> 00:59:14.510
On the counter. where it always is.

912
00:59:14.594 --> 00:59:17.597
He's in your group. right?
The. um. uh...

913
00:59:17.680 --> 00:59:19.599
- What's it called. again?
- The Justice Gang.

914
00:59:19.682 --> 00:59:21.183
- No.
- We're not called that.

915
00:59:21.267 --> 00:59:22.685
Yeah. your name is Mr. Terrific.

916
00:59:22.768 --> 00:59:24.312
You don't get a vote with a name like that.

917
00:59:24.395 --> 00:59:26.272
I also voted against it.

918
00:59:26.355 --> 00:59:29.358
Yes.
And as leader. I get tiebreaker.

919
00:59:29.442 --> 00:59:31.402
No. Superman is not officially a member.

920
00:59:31.485 --> 00:59:32.194
Because you don't want him to vote.

921
00:59:32.278 --> 00:59:33.279
You know which way that would go.

922
00:59:33.362 --> 00:59:34.572
Shut up. He's kidding.

923
00:59:34.655 --> 00:59:37.700
So. how do you even know Superman anyway?

924
00:59:38.659 --> 00:59:40.745
I... just... do.

925
00:59:40.828 --> 00:59:42.413
So you know about the hypno-glasses?

926
00:59:42.496 --> 00:59:43.623
Now she does.

927
00:59:43.706 --> 00:59:47.084
I'm not saying who he is. just
that he wears hypno-glasses.

928
00:59:47.168 --> 00:59:48.002
They make his face...

929
00:59:48.085 --> 00:59:49.128
Terrific. how do they work?

930
00:59:49.211 --> 00:59:50.671
They make his face look different

931
00:59:50.755 --> 00:59:52.256
in your brain when he wears them.

932
00:59:52.340 --> 00:59:53.341
So that you don't know who he is.

933
00:59:53.424 --> 00:59:55.134
Yes. I know this. first of all.

934
00:59:55.217 --> 00:59:57.094
But. second of all. you really
shouldn't be telling me this

935
00:59:57.178 --> 00:59:59.597
in case I don't know who he is.

936
00:59:59.680 --> 01:00:00.932
So. you know he's Clark Kent?

937
01:00:01.015 --> 01:00:03.893
Oh. my God.
Why does he trust everyone?

938
01:00:03.976 --> 01:00:07.605
He doesn't. Just us because
we are also of the cloth.

939
01:00:08.898 --> 01:00:10.024
"Of the cloth?"

940
01:00:12.234 --> 01:00:14.779
- What are we gonna do?
- About what?

941
01:00:15.071 --> 01:00:17.865
Superman! He's your friend!

942
01:00:17.949 --> 01:00:20.201
Some friend.
Came here to rule over me?

943
01:00:20.284 --> 01:00:21.953
It would be difficult to find him.

944
01:00:22.536 --> 01:00:26.332
I put nanobot GPS trackers
into Superman's bloodstream.

945
01:00:26.415 --> 01:00:28.000
You can see where his trail ends

946
01:00:28.084 --> 01:00:29.627
abruptly right here at Fort Kramer.

947
01:00:29.710 --> 01:00:32.588
a dormant military post across
the river about ten miles down.

948
01:00:32.672 --> 01:00:35.299
Even if he was dead. those
trackers would still be there.

949
01:00:35.383 --> 01:00:37.009
So. all this leads me to believe.

950
01:00:37.093 --> 01:00:38.344
as your article surmised.

951
01:00:38.427 --> 01:00:39.679
he really is in a pocket universe.

952
01:00:41.013 --> 01:00:44.100
You put nanobot GPS trackers
in your friend's bloodstream?

953
01:00:44.183 --> 01:00:45.643
Oh. I do that to everybody.

954
01:00:46.185 --> 01:00:48.771
So. okay. Come on.
Let's go to Fort Kramer then.

955
01:00:48.854 --> 01:00:50.564
The four of us. and find out what's going on.

956
01:00:50.648 --> 01:00:52.650
And then do what?

957
01:00:53.275 --> 01:00:54.860
Save him.

958
01:00:55.361 --> 01:00:56.696
You wanna break a federally

959
01:00:56.779 --> 01:00:58.656
incarcerated prisoner out of jail?

960
01:00:58.739 --> 01:01:00.324
Look. I think this is being done

961
01:01:00.408 --> 01:01:02.535
to keep him from interfering
with the Boravian invasion.

962
01:01:02.618 --> 01:01:05.079
No. you look.
I'm a Green Lantern. lady.

963
01:01:05.162 --> 01:01:07.665
That means I took a vow
not to get involved in politics.

964
01:01:07.748 --> 01:01:08.916
Oh. that's part of the vows?

965
01:01:09.000 --> 01:01:10.584
It's implied. Yeah.

966
01:01:10.668 --> 01:01:11.836
An implied vow?

967
01:01:11.919 --> 01:01:13.254
Every time there's something
he doesn't want to do.

968
01:01:13.337 --> 01:01:14.338
he says it's part of some vow.

969
01:01:14.422 --> 01:01:15.464
Oh. I swear to God.

970
01:01:15.548 --> 01:01:17.883
I am two seconds away
from forming a giant hammer.

971
01:01:17.967 --> 01:01:19.218
and beating you both to death.

972
01:01:20.261 --> 01:01:22.304
Is Supes here to take over the world?

973
01:01:22.388 --> 01:01:23.723
I don't know. Probably not.

974
01:01:23.806 --> 01:01:25.641
But the risk is just not worth the beef

975
01:01:25.725 --> 01:01:27.852
between the US government and the Justice Gang.

976
01:01:27.935 --> 01:01:29.812
Not our name.
Makes us sound like cowboys.

977
01:01:29.895 --> 01:01:31.814
But I agree with the rest.

978
01:01:32.648 --> 01:01:34.483
So you're just gonna let your friend rot

979
01:01:34.567 --> 01:01:36.360
in a pocket universe?

980
01:01:49.415 --> 01:01:51.834
That haircut should be against your vows.

981
01:01:51.917 --> 01:01:53.044
That what?

982
01:01:54.003 --> 01:01:55.588
That what should be what?

983
01:01:55.671 --> 01:01:59.508
I'll have you know 348 chicks say otherwise.

984
01:02:05.389 --> 01:02:06.140
Hey!

985
01:02:09.226 --> 01:02:09.894
What?

986
01:02:10.269 --> 01:02:12.104
I'm not saying we're gonna save him. but...

987
01:02:13.147 --> 01:02:14.899
I think we can at least check out what's going on

988
01:02:14.982 --> 01:02:16.859
with your boyfriend at this Fort Kramer.

989
01:02:16.942 --> 01:02:17.777
He's not...

990
01:02:18.903 --> 01:02:20.237
We're just seeing each other.

991
01:02:21.197 --> 01:02:21.947
But thanks.

992
01:02:22.490 --> 01:02:23.574
You want me to drive?

993
01:02:25.743 --> 01:02:27.078
We'll take my ride.

994
01:02:47.556 --> 01:02:48.849
You have a flying saucer.

995
01:02:48.933 --> 01:02:51.060
but you couldn't get a faster garage door?

996
01:02:51.936 --> 01:02:53.312
I haven't worked on that yet.

997
01:02:55.314 --> 01:02:57.817
I'm not even sure how I feel.
Honestly.

998
01:02:58.317 --> 01:03:00.736
- What?
- About Clark.

999
01:03:01.237 --> 01:03:02.655
He's not my boyfriend.

1000
01:03:02.738 --> 01:03:03.906
We've actually just been seeing each other...

1001
01:03:03.989 --> 01:03:06.117
- Yeah. lady. just to be clear.
- for a couple of months...

1002
01:03:06.200 --> 01:03:07.660
I'm not into people's emotions.

1003
01:03:07.743 --> 01:03:09.328
Yeah. no. totally.

1004
01:03:09.829 --> 01:03:11.038
I'm just thinking out loud.

1005
01:03:11.664 --> 01:03:13.290
I was gonna break up with him. actually.

1006
01:03:13.374 --> 01:03:15.042
I mean. we had this huge fight.

1007
01:03:15.126 --> 01:03:17.628
and he told me he loved me. and it just didn't...

1008
01:03:26.679 --> 01:03:29.056
Q&A time. alien.

1009
01:03:33.102 --> 01:03:34.937
Today we have a special guest.

1010
01:03:35.020 --> 01:03:38.149
I'm familiar with him.

1011
01:03:40.192 --> 01:03:44.029
And the smell of his piss
as we flew across the desert.

1012
01:03:44.113 --> 01:03:45.447
That is a lie!

1013
01:03:45.531 --> 01:03:48.075
No. not Vasil.
He's just here as an observer.

1014
01:03:50.911 --> 01:03:52.705
Mali.

1015
01:03:52.788 --> 01:03:57.084
Now. the US government
has a few questions for you.

1016
01:03:57.168 --> 01:04:00.296
Luthor. I barely know him.
He gave me food one time.

1017
01:04:01.630 --> 01:04:03.632
Who are you working with here on Earth?

1018
